subSubSection.paragraph:
Gonothecae in 

D. disticha

, resembling inverted Chinese lanterns, usually occur on the hydrorhiza. They may also arise from internodes of the hydrocaulus or even from old hydrothecae (
Calder 1971
; 
Galea 2008
). In the latter case, their morphology is atypical in being sac-shaped with a rounded distal end, they vary in length and width, and their walls are smooth or only slightly undulated (
Galea 2008
).
